defaulta sensitivity
default on this analysis, reducing it by half. When we reduced it by half, the net economic gain per annum was £12 billion, not £15 billion. The Department for Transport has reduced it by a third. We would expect that impact in isolation to have reduced the overall number, but there are other things that would push the number up again, because when this initial analysis was undertaken we had not looked at labour participation. We had not looked at the international dimension. We had not looked at freight. Again, those things could put it up. The list of things that would put the number up is longer than the ones we know about that would reduce it.
