defaultJohn defaultThursodefault:default What I am trying to find out is if any of you understand capacity on the railway and the function of speed in capacity. That is the question.
defaultProfessor Grahamdefault: I am not an expert on capacity in the railways. I really came here to talk about the statistics underpinning the—
defaultDr defaultWellingsdefault: As a general rule in increasing speed, beyond a certain point there is an optimum speed in terms of capacity because of the braking distances and so on, but that can be changed by signalling and new technology can bring things together.
